 and Language -- tAppendix D: Wisconsin Professional Development Plan Example -- tGlossary -- tReferences -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book provides educators with an accessible guide to best practices concerning content-based instruction (CBI) models and their use in English learner inclusive classrooms. The author effectively bridges the gap between theory and practice with a critical analysis of practical examples and diverse strategies for the inclusion of English learners into K-12 general education courses. The book also raises controversial questions regarding who is qualified to teach English learners and who is responsible for doing so, looking at the difficulties faced by both general educators and ESL teachers in Inclusive Classrooms. By providing a lens through which both ESL teachers and general educators are able to analyze, compare and contrast a range of widely-employed CBI methods, this book allows teachers to make informed decisions in their EL program development and work with English learners in K-12 schools.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aInclusive education. 0aInterdisciplinary approach in education. 0aLanguage artsxCorrelation with content subjects. 7aEDUCATION / Inclusive Education.2bisacsh  aContent-Based Instruction.  aContent-based ESL Instruction.  aEFL teachers.  aELL teachers.  aELs.  aESL teachers.  aEducation.  aEnglish learners.  aInclusion.  aK-12.  aProgram Development.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060670640uhtt